\newlabel{fig:capability}{{6}{19}{Increasing AI capability: the automation frontier expands. As $I^*$ rises (AI improves), a wider range of tasks receives AI supply, strengthening the supply-dilution channel for exposed workers while raising $\bar Y$ for all}{figure.6}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Non-monotone AI supply. When $s(i)$ is not uniformly decreasing, the set of workers experiencing wage compression (where supply dilution dominates output expansion) need not be an interval $[0,I^*)$ but can be a union of segments across the task distribution.}}{20}{figure.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:multiple}{{7}{20}{Non-monotone AI supply. When $s(i)$ is not uniformly decreasing, the set of workers experiencing wage compression (where supply dilution dominates output expansion) need not be an interval $[0,I^*)$ but can be a union of segments across the task distribution}{figure.7}{}}
